commit.message:
fix defaults for mingw builds

* we have to set BOOST_USE_WINDOWS_H=1 because of this bug: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/18134148
* remove '/EHsc' and '/FORCE' when compiling with mingw instead of msvc
Remove setup_requires to avoid dependency resolution issues with Poetry

Update to latest aksetup

Includes changes equivalent to https://github.com/inducer/pycuda/pull/423

Co-authored-by: Antoine Martin <antoine@xpra.org>
Drop compute target 2.x at CUDA 11.8 for AArch64 compatibility (closes gh-415)

Add support for array sizes >=2**31 for random number generation (#414)

* Add support for array sizes >=2**31 for random number generation

* Remove unused imports

commit.message: Drop np.int from curandom for numpy deprecation
Switch np.bool -> np.bool_ to track removal in numpy
Update JIT targets (CUDA 12 deprecations, plus additions) (closes gh-402)
Upgrade to bpl-subset with upstream Py3.11 fixes (closes gh-359)
Add struct module derivation to LICENSE

Pin build-time numpy versions for Python 3.10 and 3.11

This avoid errors when trying to use with a numpy version that's older
than the one that was newest when pycuda was built. See
https://github.com/inducer/pycuda/issues/271 for background on why this
is useful.
Bump versions of various github actions components
